eNCA reporter, Lindokuhle Xulu has the story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng's health department says it doesn't have the money to retain all 8,500 medical workers brought in during the height of COVID-19. This comes after a picket at the Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital by staff over challenges at the facility. READ: Gauteng Health Department not in financial crisis -CFO The hospital's CEO however dispelled reports of food shortages. eNCA reporter, Lindokuhle Xulu shares more detaisl in the video.